Such men there have been in all countries. Amongst the Egyptians Hermes
Trismegistus holds the highest place; then come Chaldaeans, Greeks, Arabs.
Italians, Gauls, Englishmen, Dutchmen, Spaniards, Germans. Poles. Hungarians,
Hebrews, and many others. Though the aforementioned Sages wrote at different
times, and in different languages, yet their works exhibit so marvellous an
agreement, that any true philosopher may easily see that all their hearts had
been gladdened by God in the discovery of this (Philosophersâ€™) Stone.
